headline: Main Windows

The I3T interface consists mainly of two windows:

- [Workspace](https://i3t-tool.org/manual.html#workspace): Where you build and connect *blocks*.
- [Scene View](https://i3t-tool.org/manual.html#scene-view): Where you *see* the resulting 3D scene.

![These are the two main windows](ui.png)

There is also a Top Bar with menus (File, Edit, Windows, etc.) where you can:
- Open/save scenes.
- Change settings.
- Manage windows.
- Save and load workspace layouts.

Windows can be *moved* and *resized*, but we recommend keeping the default layout for now.

--
headline: Basic Controls

Workspace Controls
- *Left-click* on a block: Select a single block.
- *Left-click and drag* on a block: Move the block around.
- *Left-click and drag* on empty space: Box-select multiple blocks.
- *Right-click* on empty space: Open the *Add/Context Menu*.
- *Middle mouse button (hold and drag)*: Move in the workspace.
- *Mouse wheel*: Zoom in/out.

Scene View Controls
- *Left-click* on a model: Select the model.
- *Right-click and drag*: Rotate the camera view.
- *Middle mouse button (hold and drag)*: Move the view.
- *Mouse wheel*: Zoom in/out.

Keyboard [shortcuts](https://i3t-tool.org/manual.html#shortcuts) are available but are not necessary.

