headline: Nodes and Adding Blocks

The core of I3T is working with blocks called *nodes*.

Nodes can represent:
- Transformations (Translate, Rotate, Scale),
- 3D models,
- Cameras,
- Math and logic operations,
- Time-based functions,
- Other utilities.

![Menu to add nodes](adding.png)

To [add a block](https://i3t-tool.org/manual.html#adding-nodes):
- *Right-click* on empty Workspace and choose from the *Add Menu*.

hint: Right-click in empty Workspace to open the Add Menu and choose the blocks.

