headline: Understanding Basic Blocks

You have added:

- *Model*: A 3D object block (a cube by default).
- *Sequence*: Groups multiple transformations together.
- *Scale*: A transformation node that resizes the object.

![Added nodes](nodes.png)

These blocks work together to apply transformations to a model.

--
headline: Connecting Blocks

Each node has:
- *Inputs* (left side),
- *Outputs* (right side).

Only nodes with *compatible data types* can be connected.

![Connecting nodes](connect.png)

To [connect nodes](https://i3t-tool.org/manual.html#connecting-nodes):
- *Click and drag* from an *output* to a *matching input*.

task: Connect Sequence to Model.

hint: Drag from the output icon on Sequence to the input icon on Model.

--
headline: Using Transformations

[Transformation blocks](https://i3t-tool.org/manual.html#transformations) (like Scale) must be *inserted into Sequences*.

Otherwise, they do nothing by themselves.

task: Drag the *Scale block* into the *Sequence block*.

hint: Grab the Scale block by its title bar and drop it onto the Sequence.

--
headline: Editing Values

You can [modify transformation values](https://i3t-tool.org/manual.html#modifying-values):

- *Click and drag* a matrix value left or right to adjust it.
- *Double-click* a value to type an exact number.

For Scale transformations:
- Changing one value changes all three axes together (*synergy*).
- This ensures *uniform scaling* by default.
- You can disable synergy by *right-clicking* the Scale matrix block and unchecking *Synergies*.

task: Set the Scale matrix to scale by 2.

hint: Click and drag sideways over a matrix value or double-click to type the number.

